### Doubly-Robust AIPW (with mirai bootstrap CIs)

The doubly-robust AIPW estimator is consistent if *either* the propensity model *or* the
outcome model is correctly specified — providing valuable insurance against model misspecification.


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
# Point estimate
ate_result <- aipw_ate(claims_ps)
cat(sprintf("AIPW ATE: %.1f%% (CHF difference: %.0f)\n",
            ate_result$ate_pct, ate_result$ate_chf))
```

